.TH "rcu_idle_enter" 9 "rcu_idle_enter" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rcu_idle_enter \- inform RCU that current CPU is entering idle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rcu_idle_enter
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Enter idle mode, in other words, -leave- the mode in which RCU
read-side critical sections can occur.  (Though RCU read-side
critical sections can occur in irq handlers in idle, a possibility
handled by \fBirq_enter\fP and \fBirq_exit\fP.)

If you add or remove a call to \fBrcu_idle_enter\fP, be sure to test with
CONFIG_RCU_EQS_DEBUG=y.
